Customer Segmentation Report


Customer segmentation is a process of dividing customers into distinct groups based on shared characteristics, enabling businesses to target their 
strategies more effectively.It helps in personalizing marketing efforts, improving customer retention, and identifying profitable customer groups.

WCSS (Elbow Method) to determine the optimal number of clusters.

Clustering Results
Based on the WCSS plot, we selected 4 clusters as the optimal number.

 Insights:
Cluster 1 customers are high-value, and targeted loyalty programs can improve retention.
Cluster 2 customers are price-sensitive, and offering discounts or promotions could increase sales.
Cluster 3 includes new customers, and onboarding campaigns can help boost engagement

The segmentation revealed 4 distinct customer groups, each with unique spending patterns and preferences. 
This information can guide targeted marketing, product pricing strategies, and customer engagement campaigns